==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|housholdere}}, equivalent to {{af|en|household|-er|id2=inhabitant}}. The Buddhist sense is a {{semantic loan|en|pi|gahapati|lit=house-master|nocap=yes}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈhaʊshoʊldə(ɹ)/}}
* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-householder.wav|a=Southern England}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The owner of a [[house]].
#: {{syn|en|homeowner}}
# The [[head]] of a [[household]].
#* {{RQ:Macaulay History of England|chapter=12|passage=towns in which almost every '''householder''' was an English Protestant}}
# {{lb|en|Buddhism|Hinduism}} A [[layperson]], lay [[devotee]], {{l|pi|gahapati}}, {{l|pi|grihastha}}.

